Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and
mince @shallot{1}(minced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

== Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4
servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat
to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Steak & Broccoli ==

While rice cooks, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add steak and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over,
~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step). Remove pan from heat.

Transfer steak to one side of a #baking sheet{}.

> Swap in chicken or pork tenderloin for steak; cook chicken until browned and
> cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook pork to desired doneness, 5-7
> minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board to rest.

Toss broccoli on opposite side of sheet from steak with a drizzle of oil, salt,
and pepper.

Roast on top rack until steak is cooked through and broccoli is browned and
tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once steak is done, transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

> Season broccoli and spread across entire sheet; roast as instructed.

== Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Add shallot;
cook until softened and slightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce},
@ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to
a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in a big squeeze of lime juice to taste. Remove pan from heat; stir in
@butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice steak crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and half the cilantro. Season with salt
and pepper.

Divide rice, broccoli, and steak between plates. Top steak with pan sauce. Garnish
everything with remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Thinly slice chicken or pork against the grain.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.